papers
======

flow
----

1] Here the workflow [may be updated in future its just for sample or base version]
    - https://llvm-compiler.pages.dev/

basics/
------

1] “An Incremental Approach to Compiler Construction” by Abdulaziz Ghuloum (2006).
    - http://scheme2006.cs.uchicago.edu/11-ghuloum.pdf

2] “Essentials of Compilation: An Incremental Approach” by Jeremy G. Siek and Ryan R. Newton (2019).
    - https://www.brinckerhoff.org/clements/2194-csc431/essentials-of-compilation.pdf

llvms/
-----

1] Introduction to *LLVM*

2] LLVM : A compilation framework for lifelong Program Analysis & Transformation. [2004-01-30-CGO-LLVM]
    - https://llvm.org/pubs/2004-01-30-CGO-LLVM.html

3] LLVM Official Documentation
    - https://llvm.org/docs/

4] LLVM Language Reference Manual
    - https://llvm.org/docs/LangRef/

x86_64/
-------

1] AMD64 Architecture Programmer's Manual
    - https://www.amd.com/system/files/TechDocs/24592.pdf

2] Intel 64 and IA-32 Architectures Software Developer Manuals
    - https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/developer/articles/technical/intel-sdm.html

3] System V AMD64 ABI Specification
    - https://github.com/hjl-tools/x86-psABI/wiki/X86-psABI

4] x86-64 Instruction Set Reference
    - https://www.felixcloutier.com/x86/

optimization/
--------------

1] "Engineering a Compiler" by Cooper & Torczon (2nd Edition, 2011)
    - Classic resource on optimization techniques

2] "Advanced Compiler Design and Implementation" by Muchnick (1997)
    - Comprehensive coverage of optimization passes

3] SSA (Static Single Assignment) Form
    - https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Static_single_assignment_form

4] LLVM Optimization Passes
    - https://llvm.org/docs/Passes/

code-generation/
----------------

1] "Code Generation for RISC and CISC" - Overview
    - https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Code_generation_(compiler)

2] Register Allocation Techniques
    - Graph coloring and linear scan approaches

3] Instruction Selection & Scheduling
    - https://llvm.org/docs/CodeGenerator/

tools-and-frameworks/
---------------------

1] LLVM Project
    - https://llvm.org/

2] Clang Frontend
    - https://clang.llvm.org/

3] LLVM IR Playground
    - https://godbolt.org/

4] Compiler Explorer
    - https://gcc.godbolt.org/

parser-and-lexer/
-----------------

1] "Crafting Interpreters" - Lexing & Parsing Chapter
    - https://craftinginterpreters.com/

2] Introduction to Compiler Design - Parsing Techniques
    - Recursive descent, LL parsing, LR parsing

3] Flex & Bison Documentation
    - https://www.gnu.org/software/bison/manual/

4] ANTLR Parser Generator
    - https://www.antlr.org/

type-systems-and-semantics/
---------------------------

1] "Types and Programming Languages" by Benjamin C. Pierce (2002)
    - Comprehensive type system theory

2] "Practical Foundations for Programming Languages" by Robert Harper (2016)
    - https://www.cs.cmu.edu/~rwh/pfpl/

3] Type Checking & Inference Algorithms
    - Hindley-Milner type inference, unification

4] Polymorphism & Generics
    - Parametric, ad-hoc, and row polymorphism

program-analysis/
-----------------

1] "Principles of Program Analysis" by Flemming Nielson et al. (2015)
    - Data flow analysis, abstract interpretation

2] LLVM Analysis Framework
    - https://llvm.org/docs/Passes/#analysis

3] Control Flow Graphs (CFG)
    - https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Control_flow_graph

4] Abstract Interpretation & Static Analysis
    - https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abstract_interpretation

memory-management/
------------------

1] "Garbage Collection: Algorithms for Automatic Dynamic Memory Management" by Wilfrid Marshall (2004)
    - https://www.elsevier.com/books/garbage-collection/marshall/978-0-12-417156-5

2] Mark-Sweep, Generational, and Concurrent GC
    - Reference counting, tri-color marking

3] Memory Safety in Rust
    - https://doc.rust-lang.org/nomicon/

4] Arena Allocation & Object Pools
    - Memory efficiency techniques

debugging-and-profiling/
------------------------

1] DWARF Debugging Information Format
    - https://dwarfstd.org/

2] LLVM Debug Info
    - https://llvm.org/docs/SourceLevelDebugging/

3] Profiling Techniques
    - Sampling, instrumentation, call stack analysis

4] perf & Linux Profiling Tools
    - https://perf.wiki.kernel.org/

functional-compilers/
---------------------

1] "Implementing Functional Languages" by Simon Peyton Jones & David Lester (1992)
    - https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/publication/implementing-functional-languages-a-tutorial/

2] GHC (Glasgow Haskell Compiler) Architecture
    - https://gitlab.haskell.org/ghc/ghc/-/wikis/home

3] OCaml Compiler Design
    - https://ocaml.org/docs

4] Compilation of Lazy Languages
    - Strictness analysis, graph reduction

runtime-systems/
-----------------

1] "Virtual Machine Design and Implementation" by Smith & Nair (2005)
    - JIT compilation, bytecode interpretation

2] Java Virtual Machine Specification
    - https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jvms/se19/html/

3] LLVM JIT Compilation (MCJIT)
    - https://llvm.org/docs/MCJITDesignAndImplementation/

4] Runtime Optimization & Adaptive Compilation
    - On-stack replacement, tiered compilation

performance-tuning/
--------------------

1] "Computer Architecture: A Quantitative Approach" by Hennessy & Patterson (2017)
    - CPU caches, pipelining, branch prediction

2] "Systems Performance: Enterprise and the Cloud" by Brendan Gregg (2013)
    - Profiling, tuning, optimization strategies

3] CPU Microarchitecture Guides
    - Intel, AMD processor optimization manuals

4] Cache-Conscious Compilation
    - Memory hierarchy awareness, prefetching

formal-verification/
---------------------

1] CompCert: A Formally Verified C Compiler
    - https://compcert.org/

2] Coq Proof Assistant & Formal Verification
    - https://coq.inria.fr/

3] "Certified Programming with Dependent Types" by Adam Chlipala
    - https://adam.chlipala.net/cpdt/

4] Theorem Proving for Compiler Correctness
    - Mechanized proofs of compiler transformations

language-specific-compilers/
-----------------------------

1] Rust Compiler (rustc) Design
    - https://rustc-dev-guide.rust-lang.org/

2] Go Compiler & Runtime Architecture
    - https://golang.org/src/cmd/compile/

3] Swift Compiler Architecture
    - https://www.swift.org/compiler-stdlib/

4] V Language Compiler
    - https://github.com/vlang/v

5] Zig Compiler Design
    - https://github.com/ziglang/zig/blob/master/doc/langref.md
